cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI. 

The paper is about learning the structure of an Ising model with missing data, which is a problem in machine learning and statistics. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the form of the Interaction Screening Objective (ISO) and optimization algorithms (cs.AI). The use of unbiased estimators and stochastic gradient descent also suggests a connection to data science (cs.DS). Finally, the focus on recovering neighborhood information of the Ising model suggests a connection to social and information networks (cs.SI).
